physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and oriented, no acute distress. HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/gallops/rubs. Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezing/rales/rhonchi. Abdominal: Soft, nondistended, minimally tender in right upper quadrant, no rebound or guarding, no palpable masses. Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused.
